About dataset:¶

EDA in a real business scenario¶

This case study aims to give us an idea of applying EDA in a real business scenario. In this case study, apart from applying the techniques that we have learnt in the EDA module, we will also develop a basic understanding of risk analytics in banking and financial services and understand how data is used to minimise the risk of losing money while lending to customers.

  1. 0=Non_defaulter
  2. 1= Defaulter

Analysis (Univariate analysis for all the categorical variables ):¶

  1. Name Contract : most of the customers took cash loans

  2. Code Gender:mostly females have taken loans and they are less likely to default , so we could say that females are safer persons to target for giving loans / female default rate is below 8% or lower than male , most of loans are taken by females

  3. Name Type Suite: most of the customers were unaccompanied while taking loans /Unaccompained people have taken most of loans and default rate is approx 8.5% which is still ok safe

  4. Name Income Type: the safest segment is working , commercial assosiates and pansioners and there default rate is also low

  5. Name Education Type: higher education is the safest segment to give the loan with a default rate less than 5%

  6. Name Family Status: married people are the safest segment to give loans/target with default rate less than 8%

  7. Name Housing Type: house appartment segment are the safest to target with default rate approx 8&

  8. Occupation Type: Low Skill Labourors & Drivers has the highest defaulters , Accountants are less defaulters , Labourors and Core Staff are safer to target with a default rate >=7.5 to 10%

  9. Organization Type: Transport type 3 highest defaulter , Others & Buisness Entuty Type 3 & Self Employed are good to go with default rate around 10%

  3. If the AMT_CREDIT increases the Defaulters are decreasing
